AB  - This paper tests the propositions that the real rate of interest was constant from 1953 to 1971 and that Treasury bill yields included an efficient inflationary premium over the same period. Only the former hypothesis is rejected. Comparable results are obtained with both variable parameter regression and piecewise linear regression. Direct estimates of the real rate of interest are reported.
ER  - 
